      "description": "The SourceRouter conflates two distinct concerns: (1) where to discover edition metadata and (2) where to download the ZIP/XML payload. INLABS serves both an API for discovery (listing editions) and a download endpoint. Liferay serves a JSONWS catalog AND hosts ZIPs. The proposed resolve_sources() returns a flat list[Source] without distinguishing discovery vs download phases. This means the downloader will try to 'download from INLABS' even when only the catalog was needed from Liferay, or vice-versa. In the edge case where INLABS discovery succeeds but download fails (e.g., rate limit), the fallback list doesn't know to try Liferay download with the same edition metadata. This is a design error that will produce silent data gaps in the 25-35 day overlap window.",
      "suggested_fix": "Split SourceRouter into two explicit phases: resolve_discovery_sources(edition_date) -> list[DiscoverySource] and resolve_download_sources(edition_date, edition_metadata) -> list[DownloadSource]. DiscoverySource provides catalog/listing endpoints. DownloadSource provides the actual ZIP/XML URL. The downloader receives the resolved metadata from discovery and independently resolves download sources. This also cleanly handles the case where INLABS discovery works but download is throttled вҖ” you fall back to Liferay download using the same edition identifiers."
